105#define ES_SAFE_ADDREF(val) \
106 static_assert(std::is_class<decltype(val)>::value != true, "val must not be class/struct"); \
107 if ((val) != nullptr) \
108 { \
109 (val)->AddRef(); \
110 }
111#define ES_SAFE_RELEASE(val) \
112 static_assert(std::is_class<decltype(val)>::value != true, "val must not be class/struct"); \
113 if ((val) != nullptr) \
114 { \
115 (val)->Release(); \
116 (val) = nullptr; \
117 }
118
119#define ES_SAFE_DELETE(val) \
120 static_assert(std::is_class<decltype(val)>::value != true, "val must not be class/struct"); \
121 if ((val) != nullptr) \
122 { \
123 delete (val); \
124 (val) = nullptr; \
125 }

130 delete[](val); \
131 (val) = nullptr; \

340inline int32_t ConvertUtf16ToUtf8(char* dst, int32_t dst_size, const char16_t* src)
341{
342 int32_t cnt = 0;
343 const char16_t* wp = src;
344 char* cp = dst;
345
346 if (dst_size == 0)
347 return 0;
348
349 dst_size -= 3;
350
351 for (cnt = 0; cnt < dst_size;)
352 {
353 char16_t wc = *wp++;
354 if (wc == 0)
355 {
356 break;
357 }
358 if ((wc & ~0x7f) == 0)
359 {
360 *cp++ = wc & 0x7f;
361 cnt += 1;
362 }
363 else if ((wc & ~0x7ff) == 0)
364 {
365 *cp++ = ((wc >> 6) & 0x1f) | 0xc0;
366 *cp++ = ((wc)&0x3f) | 0x80;
367 cnt += 2;
368 }
369 else
370 {
371 *cp++ = ((wc >> 12) & 0xf) | 0xe0;
372 *cp++ = ((wc >> 6) & 0x3f) | 0x80;
373 *cp++ = ((wc)&0x3f) | 0x80;
374 cnt += 3;
375 }
376 }
377 *cp = '\0';
378 return cnt;
379}
380
388inline int32_t ConvertUtf8ToUtf16(char16_t* dst, int32_t dst_size, const char* src)
389{
390 int32_t i, code = 0;
391 int8_t c0, c1, c2 = 0;
392 int8_t* srci = reinterpret_cast<int8_t*>(const_cast<char*>(src));
393 if (dst_size == 0)
394 return 0;
395
396 dst_size -= 1;
397
398 for (i = 0; i < dst_size; i++)
399 {
400 uint16_t wc;
401
402 c0 = *srci;
403 srci++;
404 if (c0 == '\0')
405 {
406 break;
407 }
408 // convert UTF8 to UTF16
409 code = (uint8_t)c0 >> 4;
410 if (code <= 7)
411 {
412 // 8bit character
413 wc = c0;
414 }
415 else if (code >= 12 && code <= 13)
416 {
417 // 16bit character
418 c1 = *srci;
419 srci++;
420 wc = ((c0 & 0x1F) << 6) | (c1 & 0x3F);
421 }
422 else if (code == 14)
423 {
424 // 24bit character
425 c1 = *srci;
426 srci++;
427 c2 = *srci;
428 srci++;
429 wc = ((c0 & 0x0F) << 12) | ((c1 & 0x3F) << 6) | (c2 & 0x3F);
430 }
431 else
432 {
433 continue;
434 }
435 dst[i] = wc;
436 }
437 dst[i] = 0;
438 return i;
439}

445class IReference

471class ReferenceObject : public IReference
472{
473private:
474 mutable std::atomic<int32_t> m_reference;
475
476public:
477 ReferenceObject()
478 : m_reference(1)
479 {
480 }
481
482 virtual ~ReferenceObject()
483 {
484 }
485
486 virtual int AddRef()
487 {
488 std::atomic_fetch_add_explicit(&m_reference, 1, std::memory_order_consume);
489
490 return m_reference;
491 }
492
493 virtual int GetRef()
494 {
495 return m_reference;
496 }
497
498 virtual int Release()
499 {
500 bool destroy = std::atomic_fetch_sub_explicit(&m_reference, 1, std::memory_order_consume) == 1;
501 if (destroy)
502 {
503 delete this;
504 return 0;
505 }
506
507 return m_reference;
508 }
509};

526template <typename T>
527inline std::unique_ptr<T, ReferenceDeleter<T>> CreateUniqueReference(T* ptr, bool addRef = false)
528{
529 if (ptr == nullptr)
530 return std::unique_ptr<T, ReferenceDeleter<T>>(nullptr);
531
532 if (addRef)
533 {
534 ptr->AddRef();
535 }
536
537 return std::unique_ptr<T, ReferenceDeleter<T>>(ptr);

544 return std::shared_ptr<T>(nullptr);

577template <typename T>
578class RefPtr
579{
580 T* ptr_ = nullptr;
581
582 template <typename U>
583 friend class RefPtr;
584
585public:
586 RefPtr() = default;
587
588 explicit RefPtr(T* p)
589 {
590 ptr_ = p;
591 }
592
593 RefPtr(std::nullptr_t)
594 {
595 ptr_ = nullptr;
596 }
597
598 ~RefPtr()
599 {
600 SafeRelease(ptr_);
601 }
602
603 RefPtr(const RefPtr<T>& o)
604 {
605 SafeAddRef(o.ptr_);
606 SafeRelease(ptr_);
607 ptr_ = o.ptr_;
608 }
609
610 void Reset()
611 {
612 SafeRelease(ptr_);
613 }
614
615 T* operator->() const
616 {
617 return Get();
618 }
619
620 T* Get() const
621 {
622 return ptr_;
623 }
624
625 RefPtr<T>& operator=(const RefPtr<T>& o)
626 {
627 SafeAddRef(o.ptr_);
628 SafeRelease(ptr_);
629 ptr_ = o.ptr_;
630 return *this;
631 }
632
633 template <class U>
634 void operator=(const RefPtr<U>& o)
635 {
636 auto ptr = o.Get();
637 SafeAddRef(ptr);
638 SafeRelease(ptr_);
639 ptr_ = ptr;
640 }
641
642 template <class U>
643 void operator=(RefPtr<U>&& o)
644 {
645 auto ptr = o.Get();
646 o.ptr_ = nullptr;
647 SafeRelease(ptr_);
648 ptr_ = ptr;
649 }
650
651 template <class U>
652 RefPtr(const RefPtr<U>& o)
653 {
654 auto ptr = o.Get();
655 SafeAddRef(ptr);
656 SafeRelease(ptr_);
657 ptr_ = ptr;
658 }
659
660 template <class U>
661 RefPtr(RefPtr<U>&& o)
662 {
663 auto ptr = o.Get();
664 o.ptr_ = nullptr;
665 SafeRelease(ptr_);
666 ptr_ = ptr;
667 }
668
669 template <class U>
670 RefPtr<U> DownCast() const
671 {
672 auto ptr = Get();
673 SafeAddRef(ptr);
674 return RefPtr<U>(static_cast<U*>(ptr));
675 }
676
677 void* Pin()
678 {
679 SafeAddRef(ptr_);
680 return ptr_;
681 }
682
683 static void Unpin(void* p)
684 {
685 auto ptr = reinterpret_cast<T*>(p);
686 SafeRelease(ptr);
687 }
688
689 static RefPtr<T> FromPinned(void* p)
690 {
691 auto ptr = reinterpret_cast<T*>(p);
692 SafeAddRef(ptr);
693 return RefPtr<T>(ptr);
694 }
695};

771template <typename T, size_t N>
772struct FixedSizeVector
773{
774private:
775 std::array<T, N> internal_;
776 size_t size_ = 0;
777
778public:
779 T& at(size_t n)
780 {
781 assert(n < size_);
782 return internal_.at(n);
783 }
784
785 const T& at(size_t n) const
786 {
787 assert(n < size_);
788
789 return internal_.at(n);
790 }
791
792 const T* data() const
793 {
794 return internal_.data();
795 }
796
797 void resize(size_t nsize)
798 {
799 assert(nsize <= internal_.size());
800 size_ = nsize;
801 }
802
803 bool operator==(FixedSizeVector<T, N> const& rhs) const
804 {
805 if (size_ != rhs.size_)
806 return false;
807
808 for (size_t i = 0; i < size_; i++)
809 {
810 if (internal_[i] != rhs.internal_[i])
811 return false;
812 }
813
814 return true;
815 }
816
817 bool operator!=(FixedSizeVector<T, N> const& rhs) const
818 {
819 return !(*this == rhs);
820 }
821
822 size_t size() const
823 {
824 return size_;
825 }
826
827 size_t get_hash() const
828 {
829 auto h = std::hash<size_t>()(size());
830 for (size_t i = 0; i < size(); i++)
831 {
832 h += std::hash<T>()(at(i));
833 }
834 return h;
835 }
836};

1229template <class T>
1230struct CustomAllocator
1231{
1232 using value_type = T;

1234 CustomAllocator()
1235 {
1236 }
1237

1239 CustomAllocator(const CustomAllocator<U>&)
1240 {
1241 }
1242
1243 T* allocate(std::size_t n)
1244 {
1245 return reinterpret_cast<T*>(GetMallocFunc()(sizeof(T) * static_cast<uint32_t>(n)));

1248 {

1321template <typename T>
1322class StringView
1323{
1324 using Traits = std::char_traits<T>;
1325
1326public:
1327 StringView()
1328 : ptr_(nullptr)
1329 , size_(0)
1330 {
1331 }
1332
1333 StringView(const T* ptr)
1334 : ptr_(ptr)
1335 , size_(Traits::length(ptr))
1336 {
1337 }
1338
1339 StringView(const T* ptr, size_t size)
1340 : ptr_(ptr)
1341 , size_(size)
1342 {
1343 }
1344
1345 template <size_t N>
1346 StringView(const T ptr[N])
1347 : ptr_(ptr)
1348 , size_(N)
1349 {
1350 }
1351
1352 StringView(const CustomString<T>& str)
1353 : ptr_(str.data())
1354 , size_(str.size())
1355 {
1356 }
1357
1358 const T* data() const
1359 {
1360 return ptr_;
1361 }
1362
1363 size_t size() const
1364 {
1365 return size_;
1366 }
1367
1368 bool operator==(const StringView<T>& rhs) const
1369 {
1370 return size() == rhs.size() && Traits::compare(data(), rhs.data(), size()) == 0;
1371 }
1372
1373 bool operator!=(const StringView<T>& rhs) const
1374 {
1375 return size() != rhs.size() || Traits::compare(data(), rhs.data(), size()) != 0;
1376 }
1377
1378 struct Hash
1379 {
1380 size_t operator()(const StringView<T>& key) const
1381 {
1382 constexpr size_t basis = (sizeof(size_t) == 8) ? 14695981039346656037ULL : 2166136261U;
1383 constexpr size_t prime = (sizeof(size_t) == 8) ? 1099511628211ULL : 16777619U;
1384
1385 const uint8_t* data = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(key.data());
1386 size_t count = key.size() * sizeof(T);
1387 size_t val = basis;
1388 for (size_t i = 0; i < count; i++)
1389 {
1390 val ^= static_cast<size_t>(data[i]);
1391 val *= prime;
1392 }
1393 return val;
1394 }
1395 };
1396
1397private:
1398 const T* ptr_;
1399 size_t size_;
1400};

2850inline int32_t GetVertexLayoutFormatSize(VertexLayoutFormat format)
2851{
2852 int32_t size = 0;
2853 if (format == Effekseer::Backend::VertexLayoutFormat::R8G8B8A8_UINT || format == Effekseer::Backend::VertexLayoutFormat::R8G8B8A8_UNORM)
2854 {
2855 size = 4;
2856 }
2857 else if (format == Effekseer::Backend::VertexLayoutFormat::R32_FLOAT)
2858 {
2859 size = sizeof(float) * 1;
2860 }
2861 else if (format == Effekseer::Backend::VertexLayoutFormat::R32G32_FLOAT)
2862 {
2863 size = sizeof(float) * 2;
2864 }
2865 else if (format == Effekseer::Backend::VertexLayoutFormat::R32G32B32_FLOAT)
2866 {
2867 size = sizeof(float) * 3;
2868 }
2869 else if (format == Effekseer::Backend::VertexLayoutFormat::R32G32B32A32_FLOAT)
2870 {
2871 size = sizeof(float) * 4;
2872 }
2873 else
2874 {
2875 assert(0);
2876 }
2877
2878 return size;
2879}
